---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Frigidaire Refrigerator Repair Los Angeles | Gallery, Pro";
const description = "Frigidaire fridge repair across LA — Gallery, Professional, French Door, side-by-side. Electrolux-owned since 1986. $89 diagnostic waived. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/frigidaire-refrigerator-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Frigidaire still an American brand — who owns it now?",
    a: "Frigidaire is owned by Electrolux, the Swedish home-appliance parent (AB Electrolux, founded 1919 and headquartered in Stockholm). Electrolux acquired Frigidaire in 1986, consolidating the historic American refrigerator brand into its global portfolio. The Frigidaire lineup is manufactured and marketed under Electrolux North America operations, with manufacturing presence in the US. For LA repair service, this means Frigidaire refrigerators share chassis platforms with Electrolux-branded residential refrigerators — many fans, thermostats, compressors, and control boards cross-reference across the two brands. Our techs handle Frigidaire and Electrolux as platform-related service categories. See <a href='/brands/electrolux-refrigerator-repair/'>Electrolux refrigerator repair</a> for the Swedish-parent sibling's service profile."
  },
  {
    q: "What are the Frigidaire tiers — Frigidaire, Gallery, Professional?",
    a: "Frigidaire markets three tiers within its refrigerator lineup. <b>Frigidaire (base)</b> — mainstream volume platform, top-freezer and side-by-side configurations at mass-market pricing; FFHT, FFSS, FRT families are common in LA rental and apartment installs. <b>Frigidaire Gallery (mid)</b> — step-up feature set including French Door configurations, through-the-door ice + water dispenser, adjustable shelving, CoolConnect Wi-Fi on higher trims; FGHB, FGHD, FGSS families are common in LA mid-market kitchens. <b>Frigidaire Professional (upper)</b> — premium trim level with counter-depth French Door, custom-flex drawer, higher-grade finish materials; FPBS, FPRS, FPBG families land in mid-premium kitchen remodels. All three tiers share Electrolux-platform engineering at the chassis level but trim out at distinct price points. Your tier is on the exterior nameplate and model-number plate."
  },
  {
    q: "Which Frigidaire refrigerator models are most common in LA?",
    a: "By volume, Frigidaire base-tier top-freezer (FFTR, FFHT families) and side-by-side (FFSS, FFUS families) dominate our LA Frigidaire service calls — rental-property, apartment-building, and budget-mainstream kitchen installs across the Valley, East LA, South Bay, and inland markets (Pomona, West Covina, Fontana). Frigidaire Gallery French Door (FGHB, FGHD) is our second-most-common service category — Valley and Westside mid-market kitchen installs. Frigidaire Professional (FPBS, FPBG counter-depth) shows up in premium-kitchen remodels alongside KitchenAid counter-depth installs. Frigidaire compact and apartment configurations are common in ADU and rental-studio applications. The SpaceWise Organization System (adjustable shelving, drawer configurations) is a Frigidaire-distinctive platform feature on Gallery and Professional trim."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Frigidaire Gallery French Door fridge won't cool — same diagnostic as other French Doors?",
    a: "Yes, substantially similar diagnostic sequence. Frigidaire Gallery French Door (FGHB, FGHD) shares architectural conventions with other mass-market French Door brands: single evaporator fan cooling both compartments, defrost-heater + thermostat defrost cycle, damper door for airflow control, electronic main control board. Diagnostic order: (1) evaporator fan motor ($280–$440); (2) defrost heater + thermostat ($320–$480); (3) damper door ($240–$380); (4) main control board ($380–$580); (5) compressor start relay + run capacitor ($180–$280) on older units. Frigidaire-specific consideration: older Gallery French Door models (pre-2015 generations) had defrost-system designs that occasionally require defrost-drain clearing beyond standard heater replacement — our techs check for drain clog as part of the defrost diagnostic because missing that diagnostic step leads to recurring freeze-up."
  },
  {
    q: "Frigidaire ice maker slow or not making ice — what's the usual cause?",
    a: "Most common LA Frigidaire ice-maker service pattern: (1) LA's hard water accelerates filter scale — filter replacement + housing clean $160–$260; (2) water-inlet valve failure — $240–$380; (3) ice-maker module at 6–10 years — $280–$420; (4) water-line freeze in colder-garage installs — thaw + insulate $180–$260. Frigidaire Gallery and Professional models with in-door ice + water dispensers have slightly more complex service paths than Frigidaire base-tier with simple factory ice maker — dispenser actuator, switch assembly, and water-line routing through the door add diagnostic steps. Service pricing on Gallery / Professional ice-maker assemblies runs $320–$460 on module swaps. On Frigidaire base-tier (simpler factory ice maker in freezer compartment) swap is $260–$380."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Frigidaire refrigerator repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common Frigidaire bands: condenser coil clean + diagnostic $160–$260; door gasket replacement (top-freezer / side-by-side) $200–$340; door gasket (Gallery French Door) $220–$380; door gasket (Professional counter-depth) $240–$400; ice-maker module (base-tier) $260–$380; ice-maker module (Gallery / Professional) $320–$460; water-inlet valve $240–$380; evaporator fan motor $260–$420; condenser fan motor $240–$400; defrost heater + thermostat $300–$460; defrost-drain clear (Frigidaire-specific consideration on older Gallery) $220–$360; damper door $240–$380; main control board $380–$580; compressor start/run capacitor $180–$280; compressor replacement (post-warranty) $900–$1,400. Frigidaire parts pricing runs at mainstream mass-market rates comparable to Whirlpool-family and GE mainstream."
  }
];

