        building segment — the base-tier top-freezer and side-by-side configurations are workhorses across
        property-management portfolios. The brand's 1986 Electrolux acquisition gave Frigidaire access to
        Electrolux's global engineering while preserving the historic American Frigidaire nameplate. The
        three-tier structure (base, Gallery, Professional) lets Frigidaire compete across value, mid-market,
        and mid-premium segments within a single brand family, with chassis-sharing keeping parts inventory
        and service approaches consistent across tiers.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our LA Frigidaire service territory spans the full three-tier range geographically. Base-tier
        Frigidaire concentrates in rental-dense Valley areas (Panorama City, North Hills, Van Nuys, Reseda),
        East LA and Boyle Heights multifamily, South Bay rental markets (Long Beach, Torrance, Carson),
