      <h2>Frigidaire refrigerator failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Water-dispenser + ice-maker service (Gallery / Professional)</h3>
        <p>
          LA's hard water drives filter scale, inlet-valve wear, and ice-maker issues. Service pattern:
          filter + housing $160–$260, inlet valve $240–$380, ice-maker module $260–$460 depending on tier.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Defrost-drain clog on older Gallery French Door</h3>
        <p>
          Older Frigidaire Gallery French Door models (pre-2015 generations) have a defrost-drain design
          that clogs more readily than current generations. Symptom: water pooling in freezer tray, ice
          buildup on evaporator, cascading cooling failure. Drain clear + defrost-system service $220–$360.
          Distinct Frigidaire diagnostic step beyond standard defrost heater / thermostat checks.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Top-freezer cold-control drift on base Frigidaire</h3>
        <p>
          Older base-tier Frigidaire (FFTR, FFHT) with mechanical cold-control dials drift over years in
          rental-use conditions. Setpoint produces warmer compartment than dial indicates. Swap $180–$280.
          Common 8-plus-year service on rental-property installed base.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Door gasket compression loss in rental-turnover</h3>
        <p>
          Frigidaire base-tier door gaskets take more abuse in rental properties than gaskets on premium
          brands in single-owner households. Replacement $200–$340 (base) / $220–$380 (Gallery) / $240–$400
          (Professional). Common 6–8 year service on rental-installed units.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Compressor start relay + capacitor on 10-plus-year units</h3>
        <p>
          Classic start-failure pattern. Relay + capacitor swap $180–$280. Common on the Frigidaire installed
          base given the age distribution of rental-property units.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>CoolConnect Wi-Fi connectivity (Gallery / Professional higher-trim)</h3>
        <p>
          CoolConnect is Frigidaire's Wi-Fi platform on higher-trim Gallery and Professional. Disconnection
          usually reconfig-level fix, not parts ($89 diagnostic visit). Actual Wi-Fi module failure rare,
          swap $180–$280 when needed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

